abstract: RATAN DEVI sang," wrote Rabindranath Tagore, "and I forgot for a moment that I was in a London drawing room. My mind got itself transported in the magnificence of an Eastern night, with its darkness transparent yet unfathomable, like the eyes of an Indian maiden, and I seemed to be standing alone in the depths of its stillness and stars."
